\subsection{Local minimal model}
\begin{definition}\label{ec.local_minimal_model}
\uses{ec,ec.discriminant,ec.weierstrass_coeffs,nf,nf.integral}
A **local minimal model** for an {{ KNOWL('ec', 'elliptic curve') }} \(E\) defined over a {{ KNOWL('nf', 'number field') }} \(K\) at a prime \(\mathfrak{p}\) of \(K\) is a {{ KNOWL('ec.weierstrass_coeffs', 'Weierstrass equation') }} for \(E\) all of whose coefficients are {{ KNOWL('nf.integral', 'integral') }}  at \(\mathfrak{p}\), and whose {{ KNOWL('ec.discriminant', 'discriminant') }} has minimal valuation at \(\mathfrak{p}\) among all such equations.
\end{definition}


